    [Source: acme_corp_contract.txt]
    3.3 Definition of Missed Delivery
    A "Missed Delivery" shall mean any instance in which:
      (i)  the applicable Deliverable is not received by Client on or before the
           Monthly Delivery Date;
      (ii) the Deliverable received materially fails to conform to the
           Specifications set forth in Exhibit B; or
      (iii) Vendor fails to provide the required pre-delivery notice as specified
            in Section 3.2.

    [Source: escalation_policy.txt]
    3. TIER 1 — FIRST MISSED DELIVERY: FORMAL WARNING
    3.1 Trigger
    Tier 1 is triggered immediately upon confirmation that a vendor has incurred
    one (1) Missed Delivery within any rolling 30-day period.

    [Source: escalation_policy.txt]
    Advise the vendor that a second Missed Delivery within the same rolling 30-day
    period will trigger a formal dispute.

